rating\">\n				<div class=\"wporg-ratings\" aria-label=\"1 out of 5 stars\" data-title-template=\"%s out of 5 stars\" data-rating=\"1\" style=\"color:#ffb900;\"><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-filled\"></span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-empty\"></span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-empty\"></span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-empty\"></span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-empty\"></span></div>				</div>\n			</div>\n			<p class=\"reviewer\">\n				By <a href=\"https://profiles.wordpress.org/nicprussik\"><img alt=\'\' src=\'https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/c0cf1dc0e3e336b62c02c94a81d1cf04?s=16&#038;d=monsterid&#038;r=g\' srcset=\'https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/c0cf1dc0e3e336b62c02c94a81d1cf04?s=32&#038;d=monsterid&#038;r=g 2x\' class=\'avatar avatar-16 photo\' height=\'16\' width=\'16\' /></a><a href=\"https://profiles.wordpress.org/nicprussik\" class=\"reviewer-name\">nicprussik</a> on <span class=\"review-date\">December 15, 2019</span>			</p>\n		</div>\n	</div>\n	<div class=\"review-body\">I have no idea if I need an ultra-fast broad band connection, a brand new lap top or a website host that is the fastest and most expensive in the world, but my goodness how I have struggled to use ELEMENTOR. Really I have. \nIt definitely isn\'t WYSIWYG, I can make changes in the editor that don\'t show up on the page. I can\'t make changes in the live page. The font size only changes if I do it through the code..... Yes I am using a totally compatible theme, in fact it is the one Elementor suggested! So I am just tearing my hair out. Don\'t get me started on the huge gaps which appear when I press enter - CTRL Enter, or Enter just puts in a 2cm gap, not just starting a new line below. \nThe whole experience is quite frustrating, and now I have started using this Elementor thing, i guess I either have to a) delete the entire website and start again using the basic but good Gutenberg editor, or b) pay to go pr