nshot-10.png?rev=2117359\"><img src=\"https://ps.w.org/visualizer/assets/screenshot-10.png?rev=2117359\" alt=\"Block editor chart\"></a><p>Block editor chart</p></li><li><a href=\"https://ps.w.org/visualizer/assets/screenshot-11.png?rev=2117359\"><img src=\"https://ps.w.org/visualizer/assets/screenshot-11.png?rev=2117359\" alt=\"Bar settings\"></a><p>Bar settings</p></li><li><a href=\"https://ps.w.org/visualizer/assets/screenshot-12.png?rev=2117359\"><img src=\"https://ps.w.org/visualizer/assets/screenshot-12.png?rev=2117359\" alt=\"Bar settings, Series settings\"></a><p>Bar settings, Series settings</p></li><li><a href=\"https://ps.w.org/visualizer/assets/screenshot-13.png?rev=2117359\"><img src=\"https://ps.w.org/visualizer/assets/screenshot-13.png?rev=2117359\" alt=\"Bar chart\"></a><p>Bar chart</p></li></ol>\";s:7:\"reviews\";s:14937:\"<div class=\"review\">\n	<div class=\"review-head\">\n		<div class=\"reviewer-info\">\n			<div class=\"review-title-section\">\n				<h4 class=\"review-title\">Great App</h4>\n				<div class=\"star-rating\">\n				<div class=\"wporg-ratings\" aria-label=\"5 out of 5 stars\" data-title-template=\"%s out of 5 stars\" data-rating=\"5\" style=\"color:#ffb900;\"><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-filled\"></span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-filled\"></span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-filled\"></span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-filled\"></span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-filled\"></span></div>				</div>\n			</div>\n			<p class=\"reviewer\">\n				By <a href=\"https://profiles.wordpress.org/etilley\"><img alt=\'\' src=\'https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/532ddf1e2030426f42928b5fe6b3ff9a?s=16&#038;d=monsterid&#038;r=g\' srcset=\'https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/532ddf1e2030426f42928b5fe6b3ff9a?s=32&#038;d=monsterid&#038;r=g 2x\' class=\'avatar avatar-16 photo\' height=\'16\' width=\'16\' /></a><a href=\"https://profiles.wordpress.org/etilley\" class=\"reviewer-name\">etilley</a> on <span class=\"review-date\">November 14, 2019</span>			</p>\n		</div>\n	</div>\n	<div class=\"review-body\">Easy to get started and add to site. Suggest looking into why shortcodes don\'t seem to work with bbpress, but that\'s minor. Great contribution !</div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"review\">\n	<div class=\"review-head\">\n		<div class=\"reviewer-info\">\n			<div class=\"review-title-section\">\n				<h4 class=\"review-title\">Best Chart Plug-in I found</h4>\n				<div class=\"star-rating\">\n				<div class=\"wporg-ratings\" aria-label=\"5 out of 5 stars\" data-title-template=\"%s out of 5 stars\" data-rating=\"5\" style=\"color:#ffb900;\"><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-filled\"></span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-filled\"></span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-filled\"></span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-filled\"></span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-filled\"></span></div>				</div>\n			</div>\n			<p class=\"reviewer\">\n				By <a href=\"https://profiles.wordpress.org/41libertybelle\"><img alt=\'\' src=\'https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/f69f85db77bc837584f129300ed8ec6b?s=16&#038;d=monsterid&#038;r=g\' srcset=\'https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/f69f85db77bc837584f129300ed8ec6b?s=32&#038;d=monsterid&#038;r=g 2x\' class=\'avatar avatar-16 photo\' height=\'16\' width=\'16\' /></a><a href=\"https://profiles.wordpress.org/41libertybelle\" class=\"reviewer-name\">41LibertyBelle</a> on <span class=\"review-date\">October 2, 2019</span>			</p>\n		</div>\n	</div>\n	<div class=\"review-body\">All that I need - Once I realized you must add the Character/Integer to the uploaded file everything worked great.  Even able to edit font style &amp; size as well as colors - Made an awesome 3D Pie Chart for our sales manager!</div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"review\">\n	<div class=\"review-head\">\n		<div class=\"reviewer-info\">\n			<div class=\"review-title-section\">\n				<h4 class=\"review-title\">Neat attempt, but quite buggy.</h4>\n				<div class=\"star-rating\">\n				<div class=\"wporg-ratings\" aria-label=\"3 out of 5 stars\" data-title-template=\"%s out of 5 stars\" data-rating=\"3\" style=\"color:#ffb900;\"><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-filled\"></span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-filled\"></span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-filled\"></span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-empty\"></span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-empty\"></span></div>				</div>\n			</div>\n			<p class=\"reviewer\">\n				By <a href=\"https://profiles.wordpress.org/modparlor\"><img alt=\'\' src=\'https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/f81b79533c4c6aaf044543e0e0242bf8?s=16&#038;d=monsterid&#038;r=g\' srcset=\'https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/f81b79533c4c6aaf044543e0e0242bf8?s=32&#038;d=monsterid&#038;r=g 2x\' class=\'avatar avatar-16 photo\' height=\'16\' width=\'16\' /></a><a href=\"https://profiles.wordpress.org/modparlor\" class=\"reviewer-name\">modparlor</a> on <span class=\"review-date\">August 29, 2019</span>			</p>\n		</div>\n	</div>\n	<div class=\"review-body\">I just got the Pro Version for an online presence. I expected this tool to save me work over integrating ChartJS myself and entering the data manually into the JS arrays. I\'m slowing regreting my purchase as I edit this buglist for the 5th time. Bugs dimish the experience, some bugs are *really* annoying/bad.\n\nThese bugs have shown up whilst working with columcharts:\n\n- Whenever I dublicate a Chart with the ChartJS API it clones the chart but sets the Google API as default. Resulting in making some adjustments such as tick setting impossible. I have yet to find a way to change the API after a chart has been created.\n\n- Each Chart with manual data has \"Array\" as a title\n\n- Manual data doesn\'t save unless you refresh the chart view in edit mode. Hit \"Save Chart\", see overview with no changes, all work gone ... super annoying\n\n- Cloned Charts with invisible legends have their legends visible again\n\n- Text is squished in columcharts when loading them for editing\n\n- Column colors change randomly when switching between data editor and chart view. The fun part: The last new colors are automaticaly saved even though I didn\'t save them. ... WTF?\n\nMissing feature:\n- Still havent found a way to color colums individually. With the \"random surprise color\" bug from above this makes any sort of coloring an adventure and an excercise in praying and hoping.\n\n\nConclusion:\nThis still needs some serious work. This is a release candidate at best, not a finished product. Very frustrating.</div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"review\">\n	<div class=\"review-head\">\n		<div class=\"reviewer-info\">\n			<div class=\"review-title-section\">\n				<h4 class=\"review-title\">Fantastic!</h4>\n				<div class=\"star-rating\">\n				<div class=\"wporg-ratings\" aria-label=\"5 out of 5 stars\" data-title-template=\"%s out of 5 stars\" data-rating=\"5\" style=\"color:#ffb900;\"><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-filled\"></span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-filled\"></span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-filled\"></span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-filled\"></span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-filled\"></span></div>				</div>\n			</div>\n			<p class=\"reviewer\">\n				By <a href=\"https://profiles.wordpress.org/raquelordonez\"><img alt=\'\' src=\'https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/909270d0fbe59904b1ca79f557e6dcec?s=16&#038;d=monsterid&#038;r=g\' srcset=\'https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/909270d0fbe59904b1ca79f557e6dcec?s=32&#038;d=monsterid&#038;r=g 2x\' class=\'avatar avatar-16 photo\' height=\'16\' width=\'16\' /></a><a href=\"https://profiles.wordpress.org/raquelordonez\" class=\"reviewer-name\">raquelordonez</a> on <span class=\"review-date\">August 28, 2019</span>			</p>\n		</div>\n	</div>\n	<div class=\"review-body\">Excelente, me funciona!!</div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"review\">\n	<div class=\"review-head\">\n		<div class=\"reviewer-info\">\n			<div class=\"review-title-section\">\n				<h4 class=\"review-title\">Very handy tool with lots of features</h4>\n				<div class=\"star-rating\">\n				<div class=\"wporg-ratings\" aria-label=\"4 out of 5 stars\" data-title-template=\"%s out of 5 stars\" data-rating=\"4\" style=\"color:#ffb900;\"><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-filled\"></span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-filled\"></span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-filled\"></span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-filled\"></span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-empty\"></span></div>				</div>\n			</div>\n			<p class=\"reviewer\">\n				By <a href=\"https://profiles.wordpress.org/jobatkin\"><img alt=\'\' src=\'https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/f3031b3485591267209390686d2b31ad?s=16&#038;d=monsterid&#038;r=g\' srcset=\'https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/f3031b3485591267209390686d2b31ad?s=32&#038;d=monsterid&#038;r=g 2x\' class=\'avatar avatar-16 photo\' height=\'16\' width=\'16\' /></a><a href=\"https://profiles.wordpress.org/jobatkin\" class=\"reviewer-name\">Jo Batkin <small>(jobatkin)</small></a> on <span class=\"review-date\">August 28, 2019</span>			</p>\n		</div>\n	</div>\n	<div class=\"review-body\">Works well for all kinds of charts, easy to use, love the instant previews. Would give 5 stars if the colours were customisable!</div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"review\">\n	<div class=\"review-head\">\n		<div class=\"reviewer-info\">\n			<div class=\"review-title-section\">\n				<h4 class=\"review-title\">Works fine</h4>\n				<div class=\"star-rating\">\n				<div class=\"wporg-ratings\" aria-label=\"4 out of 5 stars\" data-title-template=\"%s out of 5 stars\" data-rating=\"4\" style=\"color:#ffb900;\"><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-filled\"></span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-filled\"></span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-filled\"></span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-filled\"></span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-empty\"></span></div>				</div>\n			</div>\n			<p class=\"reviewer\">\n				By <a href=\"https://profiles.wordpress.org/jamespeasle\"><img alt=\'\' src=\'https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/940400f8b345d9a83b2996f5f341fab6?s=16&#038;d=monsterid&#038;r=g\' srcset=\'https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/940400f8b345d9a83b2996f5f341fab6?s=32&#038;d=monsterid&#038;r=g 2x\' class=\'avatar avatar-16 photo\' height=\'16\' width=\'16\' /></a><a href=\"https://profiles.wordpress.org/jamespeasle\" class=\"reviewer-name\">jamespeasle</a> on <span class=\"review-date\">August 15, 2019</span>			</p>\n		</div>\n	</div>\n	<div class=\"review-body\">Helped me in creating nice charts, but since I am a novice, it took a while.</div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"review\">\n	<div class=\"review-head\">\n		<div class=\"reviewer-info\">\n			<div class=\"review-title-section\">\n				<h4 class=\"review-title\">Works like expected</h4>\n				<div class=\"star-rating\">\n				<div class=\"wporg-ratings\" aria-label=\"5 out of 5 stars\" data-title-template=\"%s out of 5 stars\" data-rating=\"5\" style=\"color:#ffb900;\"><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-filled\"></span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-filled\"></span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-filled\"></span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-filled\"></span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-filled\"></span></div>				</div>\n			</div>\n			<p class=\"reviewer\">\n				By <a href=\"https://profiles.wordpress.org/bhenselmann\"><img alt=\'\' src=\'https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/894e1744f93665d1984ed0cd3a2a2dd1?s=16&#038;d=monsterid&#038;r=g\' srcset=\'https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/894e1744f93665d1984ed0cd3a2a2dd1?s=32&#038;d=monsterid&#038;r=g 2x\' class=\'avatar avatar-16 photo\' height=\'16\' width=\'16\' /></a><a href=\"https://profiles.wordpress.org/bhenselmann\" class=\"reviewer-name\">bhenselmann</a> on <span class=\"review-date\">August 14, 2019</span>			</p>\n		</div>\n	</div>\n	<div class=\"review-body\">I changed from RJ Quickcharts to the Visualizer plugin, because RJ Quickcharts was not longer maintained. There are some advantages and some disadvantages of both, but the main advantage of Visualizer is, that it is available for actual WordPress and PHP versions.</div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"review\">\n	<div class=\"review-head\">\n		<div class=\"reviewer-info\">\n			<div class=\"review-title-section\">\n				<h4 class=\"review-title\">ÐžÑ‚Ð»Ð¸Ñ‡Ð½Ñ‹Ð¹ Ð¿Ð»Ð°Ð³Ð¸Ð½.</h4>\n				<div class=\"star-rating\">\n				<div class=\"wporg-ratings\" aria-label=\"5 out of 5 stars\" data-title-template=\"%s out of 5 stars\" data-rating=\"5\" style=\"color:#ffb900;\"><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-filled\"></span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-filled\"></span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-filled\"></span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-filled\"></span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-filled\"></span></div>				</div>\n			</div>\n			<p class=\"reviewer\">\n				By <a href=\"https://profiles.wordpress.org/memnokh\"><img alt=\'\' src=\'https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/cd86ac19bc3d3c89fbc304f49aca63e6?s=16&#038;d=monsterid&#038;r=g\' srcset=\'https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/cd86ac19bc3d3c89fbc304f49aca63e6?s=32&#038;d=monsterid&#038;r=g 2x\' class=\'avatar avatar-16 photo\' height=\'16\' width=\'16\' /></a><a href=\"https://profiles.wordpress.org/memnokh\" class=\"reviewer-name\">memnokh</a> on <span class=\"review-date\">June 24, 2019</span>			</p>\n		</div>\n	</div>\n	<div class=\"review-body\">Ð›ÐµÐ³Ð¾Ðº Ð² Ð¾Ð±Ñ€Ð°Ñ‰ÐµÐ½Ð¸Ð¸ Ð¸ Ð½Ð°ÑÑ‚Ñ€Ð¾Ð¹ÐºÐµ Ð² Ð½ÑƒÐ¶Ð½Ñ‹Ð¹ Ð²Ð¸Ð´.</div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"review\">\n	<div class=\"review-head\">\n		<div class=\"reviewer-info\">\n			<div class=\"review-title-section\">\n				<h4 class=\"review-title\">Does what it says</h4>\n				<div class=\"star-rating\">\n			